🚨 PROJECT RELEASE🚨

This video was one of those projects that gave me life because of how much fun I had while working on it.

Not every job is one that’s going to creatively charge you. Not ever photo or video I edit is going to make me fall in love with my craft.

It’s those few videos that come through here and there that lift you up out of a creative rut, and this video was that one for me.

I tried new things that I’ve always wanted to try on my own, I experimented with different editing techniques, and honestly, the band and I just wanted to make something that looked cool as hell.

And that was the goal.

So excited for everyone to finally see what we’ve been cooking up. Let me know what y’all think in the comments here, it would mean a lot.

Also, I know I’ve kind of been a ghost on here for a few weeks (maybe months? Idk it’s hard out here ok) but I’ve been working on a lot of cool stuff on the back end that I will share with you all soon.

Thanks for reading/watching. You are the best 🖤

I did it.

75 outside work outs (45 min each)- no matter the weather conditions.

75 indoor workouts (45 min each)

750 pages read - non fiction books only.

75 gallons of water down.

Stick to a diet for 75 days - no cheat meals / no alcohol.

75 progress pictures taken.

It was one hell of a journey but I made it through.

75 Hard = COMPLETE. ✔️ 

My weight on day 1 was 181 lbs. My weight on day 75 was 163 lbs.

I started to reach a point where I started to really hate the way I looked, and it destroyed my self confidence. So what better way to fight that mentality with a MENTAL TOUGHNESS challenge? It changed not only my physical appearance, but my mental game more than anything.

If there’s ONE thing I have learned about doing this program, it’s that you DO have time in the day to accomplish the goals you set out to achieve. No excuses. You can do it.

Get off your butt and do something creative 📸 

6 things I want to share with everyone today regarding photography/filmmaking/content creation.

1. The days where you’re feeling lazy are the days you SHOULD go shoot. I wasn’t feeling like shooting at ALL yesterday, but I got off my butt and went downtown to take some photos with my buddy @brandonmperez and it was exactly what I needed. It wasn’t something I normally do, but I needed to change it up to reset my brain.

2. Inspiration isn’t going to come to you, unless your actively seeking it. It will only find you when you’re working.

3. Stop waiting to put your content out there. Just post it.

4. IF you are trying to GROW: Posting reels gives you WAY more organic reach than just posting photos. I know, “you don’t wanna have to worry about video.” Well get over it. Play the game or lose.

5. Don’t be discouraged if your numbers don’t do well. You’ll never hit a home run if you never get up to bat. So get up to bat. Post that video.

6. STOP posting long form content on a SHORT form content platform. 5-15 seconds is all you need. But if you want to post something longer, go for it. This is strictly speaking to creators who are trying to grow.

I need to practice what I preach and post more of my own content and convert it to short form. So here I am, putting it out there. Even if it’s not what I normally do, I had fun doing it. And I’m sharing it because I believe in it, and idgaf if it’s not in my niche. 

I’ve shared a lot more of what I’ve learned about social media and content creation with a few artists and they’ve seen significant growth with their accounts. A lot of what I post are typically tests to see what works and what doesn’t.

If you’d like me to create a long form video about this stuff, I totally will. But I gotta know if it’s worth it. So comment here and tell me if it’s something you’re curious about and I’ll be happy to share what I’ve learned.

If you’ve read this far you are super cool. Let’s be friends 💪🏼🖤

AI video animation test 🤖

Messing around with AI tools has been something I’ve wanted to integrate with my creative work flow for awhile now.

AI scares a lot of people, thinking that it’s going to take away the jobs of a lot of creatives. BUT I like to think of it as an extra tool in my arsenal to create better videos for my clients.

Creating something like this from scratch would have taken countless hours, when instead it only took a few moments. Absolutely wild.

I don’t think adding something like this in your workflow will take away from the creative outputs of human creativity. It’s all about the way it’s compiled together as an end result, that will make it stand out to viewers, and ultimately that will be determined by human decisions (which could take hours of trial and error, but that will give a better outcome in the end)

Leaning into this world, instead of rejecting it. Move forward, not backward.

Excited to see how this tech advances!

#ai #aianimation #animation #aiart #technology #videocreator

🌴Take a vacation 🌴 

One thing that I think should be a top priority for all photographers & filmmakers, would be to escape for a little bit, take a vacation, and take some shots for yourself.

No clients, no deadlines, no rules.

Remember why you picked up a camera in the first place.

Reset, create, repeat.

These shots were filmed with the @djiglobal Mavic Pro 2 at sunset in Tavares, FL while on a family vacation.

I didn’t get too many shots because I was focused on being present with my family. But this sunset was too good not to capture. Again, filming just for me.

Have a good day ✌🏻

Shot on my iPhone 15 Pro Max- @roosevelt_music in Detroit last night 🤙🏻

As a photographer that got started in the music scene, typically anytime I go to a show, I get the itch to bring my camera with me and snap a few shots of the band playing.

Last night I went to a show, and I did NOT bring my camera with me, so I could be 100% present with the music. 

I’ve been wanting to see Roosevelt live for a hot min, and I finally was able to last night with my wife and sister.

BUT I couldn’t help myself, and still snapped a few photos with the camera I had on me.

I edited everything with Lightroom mobile. Sometimes simplicity goes a long way 🤙🏻

Should I still upgrade to the new one this year? Or stick it out for the 16? 😂
